<DIV class=3DblogComment><A name=3D3045612117455741255></A>Only guesses =
about the=20
CleverAge ODF addin, but still :<BR><BR>- written in .NET, so incurs a =
few=20
seconds just to load<BR>- not written with performance in mind, meaning =
bad=20
String use all over the place. Effect : many garbage collections, a big =
time=20
consumer.<BR>- inefficiency of the resulting translated file. To store =
strings=20
and numbers, there are ways Excel optimizes it (shared strings, =
factorized=20
floats, single precision floats versus double precision floats). This =
greatly=20
impacts both the file size, and the time to open it in its native=20
application.<BR><BR>-Stephane Rodriguez<BR>
